list.comment: Fixed the X to Fill in Here and made it red by changing strong to strikethrough. But It makes the label red on creation. Maybe I can leave it.

task.summary: Default task
Tried to add new features like Deleting but not working. Overall besides that it is a full working copy.
changed '/new' to '/form'
Added deletion of localStorage items and fixed other bugs
Added saving on form creation
Fixed saving on form creation. Also added modal that asks if you want to save
Fixed validation for spaces
made header width 200% because when width is 700px it only goes halfway
Removed the 200% thing on both the form control and header
got rid of directly changing state instead of using setState in FormsContainer and other warnings
Added form requirements and validation for the FormsContainer
Fixed a duplicate title in the JSON constants file
Added delete form when user discards it when pressing back button - only if form is empty
Added Advanced Form Editing - React quill
Minor changes
Added basic fill in the blank functionality
Removed the fill in the blank.
Added static fields

Added Basic Fill in the Blank Functionality --> Instead of 3 months - I added X months. It detects if the X is there and bold, otherwise it sends you to the next page.
Basically doesn't let you submit the form until its not there.
When discarding, the whole form gets discarded, not just new changes so I fixed that
Attempting to add a table for Documentation of Informed Consent
Added Table for Informed Consent but the Validation for the study title needs to be added
Fixed the fill in the blank: Removed all the code in FormTextArea and replaced it with a single function in FormContainer that loops through the array and checks if it contains the Bold X
Validates every Form except funder and co-investigators. If it is not empty it submits
This is the potential working version of the validation of forms

Release: Add Validation * or something to display that the form needs to be validated
Fully working
Added sorting to Startup Form
Added a footer to each page when printing. But it is a sticky footer so the next step is to make it not sticky
I got the Date to work even when scrolling but the page number doesn't show.
The version number works but not the Page count

Added Image uploading functionality. My code works but it needs to be cleaned up.
It checks if it has reached 2 files,
I cleaned up the code, it works. On save I now save the images too which then the ConsentForm.js now can read in state. The next step is displaying the photos in the ConsentForm
Now I am converting the image to base64. This way the forms can read it as a file later. But i stillhaven't been able to convert it back from base64 to File
I was able to convert back to File type form base64. I also added another property called base64FileNames which keeps track of the file names for every image.
Added Adding Images to the Image Header. But now there are performace issues when typing in the forms

I fixed the performace issue. I added shouldComponentUpdate and made it so the forms that are not being edited do not update. I also moved out the container and label for quill out so it can still be validated. If it isn't updated in the component, then it wont show a Red Label if it is not valid.
Date is now being loaded from Local Storage and being set as the start date: so when you reload or go back the date wont be reset to today's date
Working Version with Date Picker and Image Uploader
Added savedFormName to eConsent which basically changed the formName to itself plus the date
I actually refactored it: instead of adding it to the forms Container, I add the date tot the formName in the StartUp Form
Added: When date is changed, and then saved, a copy of the Form is mad
When I change the date and save -- which creates a new form, when i then save it, the original date is not the same as the actual date.
This is a version of the Change Date, and Save Copy. Working. Bugs not found or tested yet.

Bugs tested and working except for one bug: on date change -> direct submit -> back to forms, then save, it scrolls to the top. Basically the .prop.date is the last forms date. Even though in React Tools it is the same and startDate. Why is the props not correct? Not a huge issue. Just a rare case where it scrolls to the top
Added base code for duplication
Refactored the FormsContainer. Moved everyhting to separate components. Added more basecode to the duplicate.
Added duplication working.
Working version
Fixed Design. Untested
